cbc]\r\nerror: Exiting.\r\nTrace/breakpoint trap\r\n```\r\n\r\nI can reproduce this reliably, and it happens with a number of different queries, which have in common that they contain a ReQL branch term.\r\nThe backtrace does not seem stable. I get a different one every time, and sometimes no backtrace at all.\r\n\r\nI have experimented a bit and the problem seems to be associated with using the default database in the test part of the branch. Here is a much simpler query that you can use to test and reproduce the problem:\r\n\r\n1. This one works, no crash:\r\n```\r\n    r.branch(r.table('metaData').get('HomePage').contains('versions'), r.expr(true), r.expr(false))\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. This one also works, no crash (note that we select the db explicitly):\r\n```\r\n    r.branch(r.db('test').table('metaData').get('HomePage').contains('versions'), r.table('metaData').get('HomePage'), r.expr(false))\r\n```\r\n\r\n3. This one crashes the server:\r\n```\r\n    r.branch(r.table('metaData').get('HomePage').contains('versions'), r.table('metaData').get('HomePage'), r.expr(false))\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn both cases, prepare the database as follows:\r\n```\r\nr.db('test').tableCreate('metaData', {primaryKey:'pagename'})\r\nr.table('metaData').insert({pagename: 'HomePage', versions: [1]})\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAppendix: The specific query that triggered the crash from above was this one (in PHP-RQL):\r\n\r\n```\r\n$metaData = r\\table('metaData')->get($pagename);\r\n        \r\n// If no version information is stored, default to 0\r\n$versionExistsTest = $metaData->ne(null)->rAnd($metaData->contains('versions'));\r\n$defaultVersions = r\\expr(array(0));\r\n        \r\n// Get the versions field.\r\n$versionsQuery = $metaData('versions');\r\n        \r\n$versions = r\\branch($versionExistsTest, $versionsQuery, $defaultVersions)->run($this->conn)->toNative();\r\n```\r\n"
